    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="825"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d825">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has received your dispatch of this date and awaits your letter.
                    Meantime, however, the question may be ultimately determined. He assumes you
                    have not yielded the claim by right of conquest. In fact, the destruction of the
                    Spanish fleet on May 1 was the conquest of Manila, the capital of the
                    Philippines. The President has confidence that the Commission will be able to
                    make a treaty on just and honorable grounds. A failure to do so would be greatly
                    to be regretted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
